.Dd 
.Dt RINDEX 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm rindex
.Nd locate character in string
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Fd #include <string.h>
.Ft char *
.Fn rindex "const char *s" "int c"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn rindex
function
locates the last character
matching
.Fa c
(converted to a
.Em char )
in the null-terminated string
.Fa s .
.Sh RETURN VALUES
A pointer to the character is returned if it is found; otherwise
NULL is returned.
If
.Fa c
is
.Ql \e0 ,
.Fn rindex
locates the terminating
.Ql \e0 .
